        <div class="description">
          <p>Apparently, people spend 18 minutes a day scrolling Netflix in search of something to watch. This, combined with the demands of cooking, can be pretty annoying on a Friday night. Enter <%= link_to "126", "http://www.onetwosix.co.uk/", class: "project-link", target: "_blank" %>. The user simply has to add their postcode, combine a movie genre and food type and then browse through the combos provided by the app. Every restaurant that delivers in the area will be included as an option. Once a combo is chosen it will take the user to the movie on Netflix and to the restaurant on Deliveroo.</p>
          <p> We achieved these features by scraping the Deliveroo platform for open restaurants corresponding with the chosen cuisine and within the postcode entered, and by parsing Netflix movie titles by genre using an API. An automated Youtube search for movie trailers was incorporated. As a perk for restaurant owners on Deliveroo, we built an option to join the platform as a sponsor and create a combo of their own restaurant and a film to increase their order numbers. The app is hosted by Heroku.</p>
          <p>Our team of four built this app in less than 10 days, during the last two weeks of the Le Wagon bootcamp. We had already decided on the flow and on the overall user journey previously, using Figma and Whimsical, but during production I styled the site, made it responsive on all devices and integrated the carousel using JavaScript. On demo night my team and I presented the app in front of an audience at the Google Start-up Campus in London.</p>
        </div>
